<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 16:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Hostages Killed in Rescue Clash in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Three hostages were killed and
three others injured on Tuesday in the rescue operation when
Yemeni security forces stormed the hideout of their Islamic
extremist kidnappers.
</P>
<P>
Two British men and an American woman were killed during the
exchange of fire that ensued. The other 13 hostages were freed,
but two British men and an Australian man were wounded, a Yemeni
security official said on condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
Two of the kidnappers and a policeman were also killed in the
shootout, while another kidnapper and three policemen were
wounded, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The 16 Westerners -- 12 Britons, six of whom women, two American
women and two Australian men -- were taken hostage on Monday near
the southern Yemeni town of Mawdiyah, 200 kilometers south of
Sanaa, when 18 men ambushed the convoy of the tourists.
</P>
<P>
The kidnappers, who were identified by Yemeni security
officials as members of the extremist Islamic Jihad, demanded the
release of two of their leaders who were arrested during Yemeni
government's recent crackdown on Islamic extremists.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni authorities began negotiations with the abductors
earlier Tuesday for the release of the tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
