<DOCNO> XIE19981230.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: U.N. Faces Challenges of Peace, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 29 (Xinhua) -- On the other hand,
Annan, who described the globalization process as "the dominant
features of our times," said that the global economic and
financial crisis is one of the main challenges facing the world
body in the coming year.
</P>
<P>
The connection between the double challenge is too clear.
Unless the United Nations tackles the underlying distortions and
imbalances in the global economy -- unless the Organization starts
to provide the kind of "global governance" which is needed -- the
world must expect conflicts and even more intractable ones.
</P>
<P>
At present, economic and political security are, and always
have been, closely interconnected. When the world is encountering
uncertainties and difficulties in politics and economy, people
will naturally turn their eyes to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations, as the only global organization in the
world, bears "special responsibility" in the globalization
process, which has seen the developing countries, the least
developed countries in particular, getting more and more
marginalized in the world economic community.
</P>
<P>
In fact, only few countries benefit from the process of
globalization. Therefore, a lot of developing countries, long
haunted by poor terms of trade and mounting pressure of huge
debts, have been crying out for a more balanced development of the
world economy.
</P>
<P>
The long-cherished aspiration can only be achieved with the
assistance of the the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The world body, which has the convening power, can bring all
countries into discussion of the issues of global economy, as it
organized a high-level dialogue on the world economy in September
on the sidelines of the 53rd General Assembly session.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations is expected to play a central role in the
world efforts to restore market confidence, to stabilize financial
markets and to provide immediate protection for the most
vulnerable.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 18 months, there are quite a lot of discussions
about the world financial system, or what some people called the
world financial architecture. Some of the discussions were held
under the U.N. auspices in order to find a global solution to the
global problem.
</P>
<P>
However, the ambitions and capabilities of the United Nations
are very much confined due to a large amount of back dues. The
international community has called on the countries which are in
arrears to make "prompt payment" of their contributions. At
present, the United States is the largest debtor to the United
Nations, and it just saved its voting right in the General
Assembly next year by paying the minimum amount of money the
Charter requires.
</P>
<P>
In order to better deal with the double challenges, the United
Nations will spend much time next year on the preparation of the
Millennium Assembly, to be convened in the Year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that he would spend much of next year on his report
on the U.N. role in the new century. As part of preparations, the
United Nations is going to hold informal events or hearings in
various regional centers, involving Member States as well as
non-governmental organizations and the private sectors.
</P>
<P>
"I hope those events will throw up many new and useful ideas on
the objectives of the United Nations in the decade ahead, in all
five areas of its work, peace and security, economic and social
affairs, development cooperation, humanitarian action, and of
course human rights," he added.
</P>
<P>
In General, the United Nations is in a better position to
answer the global calls for a new world economic and political
order in order to usher a more developed, prosperous and peaceful
world into the new century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
