<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eiffel Tower Breaks Record in Receiving Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The Eiffel Tower broke the world
record in the number of visitors in 1998 by receiving 6 million
people, said the Societe d'Exploitation of la Tour which runs
tourism of the 110-year-old tower.
</P>
<P>
In France, the Eiffel Tower was followed in the number of
visitors by the Louvre Arts Museum with 3.6 million visitors and
the Chateau de Versailles with 2.3 million in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Some 70 percent of visitors on Eiffel are foreigners, with
North Americans making up 13 percent, British 12 percent, and
Germans 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the weekend of la Toussaint festival last month, the
tower earned 800,000 francs (150,000 U.S. dollars) and it earns
one million francs (170,000 dollars) a day during festival days.
</P>
<P>
The other most visited monuments in the world include the
Empire State Building in New York with 3.6 million visitors and
the Tokyo Tower in Tokyo with 3 million visitors in 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
