<DOCNO> XIE19981230.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's PM Urges to Overcome Difficulties and </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minster Phan Van Khai
Tuesday urged Vietnamese people to make greater efforts to
overcome difficulties and challenges as well as weaknesses of the
national economy itself and shortcomings in the state management
of economic activities.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview to Vietnam News Agency, Khai said the
situation in 1999 will be " unpredictable" and Vietnam "will have
to face even greater difficulties and challenges next year."
</P>
<P>
He said complicated developments in the regional financial
crisis in May have "further adverse impact" on Vietnam's economy.
Unpredictable weather conditions have caused severe natural
calamities in Vietnam and other countries in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Khai said his government laid stress on the policy to bring
into full play the people's great potential, care for and develop
the close relations between the party, the state and the people,
and unceasingly strengthen political stability, thus taking the
country forward in any circumstances.
</P>
<P>
The declining trend in foreign direct investment will continue
in the future. It will take more time for a number of Vietnam's
major investors to overcome difficulties caused by the crisis and
revitalize their own economies, said the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
In that situation, he said, the domestic capital resources play
a more decisive role in attaining projected economic growth
targets.
</P>
<P>
Khai believed that Vietnam has been able to overcome those
difficulties and challenges by bringing into full play the
people's intellectual and material strength, and expanding
international cooperation for the benefits of the national
economy.
</P>
<P>
Relying on the people and fully liberalizing their labor,
raising the people's confidence in the party's and state's line
and policies and encouraging them to work for their own benefits
and for the prosperity of the nation, that is the basic solution
to create a new momentum to take the country out of the
difficulties and challenges ahead and advance into the 21st
century with an improved position and strength, Khai concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
