<HEADLINE> U.S. Reserve Assets Increase to 79.79 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Washington, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Treasury
Department said that U.S. official reserve assets rose 282 million
U.S. dollars to 79.79 billion dollars in the week ended December
18, according to a report of the Wall Street Journal on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Department said that in the previous week the increase of
reserve assets was 1.12 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. reserve assets consist of foreign currencies, gold,
special drawing rights at the International Monetary Fund and the
U.S. reserve position at the IMF.
</P>
<P>
The nation's holdings of foreign currencies decreased 26
million U.S. dollars for the week to 35.58 billion dollars,while
its gold reserves were unchanged at 11.04 billion dollars. U.S.
holdings of IMF special drawing rights increased 23 million U.S.
dollars to 10.55 billion dollars, and its reserve position at the
IMF rose 285 million U.S. dollars to 22.61 billion dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
