<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-one people died
and 33 others sustained heavy and light injuries when a
low-capacity truck overturned in southern Ethiopia Monday,
according to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted local police as saying that the truck
traveling from Dilla to Chuko was carrying 56 people when it
overturned at a place called Bonkoka, some 360 kilometers south
of the capital Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
Most of the passengers had left home to celebrate the Chachu
Gebriel religious ceremony. Only two passengers had escaped
unscathed.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident has not yet been established, but
the police suspect that the driver might have been drunk, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, a similar road accident occurred in eastern
Ethiopia with four people killed instantly and others sustained
injuries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the accident took
place when a public transport bus plunged into a 55 meter deep
ravine near Asebe-Teferi, over 35 kilometers east of Addis Ababa.
