the no-fly zone. The no-fly zone prevents Saddam (Hussein) from
using his own aircraft to oppress his people and threaten his
neighbors. This remains a key element of our containment policy
and we will aggressively enforce it," Leavy said.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, President Bill Clinton said the U.S. attack on the
Iraqi missile battery was appropriate and that the United States
would continue to enforce no-fly zones in the north and south of
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has said its missiles had downed a Western plane during
the exchange of fire. But both the United States and Britain
denied and said their patrolling planes had returned safely to
their air base in Turkey.  
</P>
