LUANDA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Angola's military sources said
Tuesday fighting still raged on in central Angola where the rebel
National Union for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) launched
counter-attacks despite government's recovery of strategic areas.
</P>
<P>
According to Simione Mucume, commander for Bie Province, when
several hundred UNITA soldiers started a sneak attack on Cunhinga
town, 30 kms north of Kuito Monday, government troops repulsed
them, killing tens of UNITA soldiers and capturing two bmp-2
armored vehicles, seven rocket launchers and some light weapons.
</P>
<P>
The government forces re-captured Cunhinga which has long been
regarded as gate to Kuito City on December 22, after killing 200
UNITA soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Besides, UNITA men shelled Cunje Town, about seven kms from
Kuito also Monday with intensive rocket bombs, but withdrew after
suffering heavy losses.
</P>
<P>
Fierce fighting was centered around the strategic points
around Huambo, capital of Huambo province.
</P>
<P>
According to Armando Silva, Deputy Governor of the Province,
UNITA forces tried to capture Calenga Town about 30 kms west of
Huambo, but were driven back by the heavy fire power of the
government forces.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said the military conflicts in central Angola
have spread to Huila Province, south of Huambo and Cuando-Cubango
Province south of Bie Province Monday, where UNITA men were seen
moving about in villages and on main roads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
