<HEADLINE> Ghanaian Travelers Advised to Know More About </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Ghana's Foreign Ministry
Tuesday advised would-be travelers to China to seek adequate
information about conditions in that country before embarking on
their trips or missions.
</P>
<P>
In a release issued in Accra, the ministry said acquiring
sufficient knowledge about China would help save travelers from
"unnecessary difficulties and inconveniences," a special story
sent by Ghanaian News Agency (GNA) to Xinhua based here said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The release said some Ghanaians travel to China for various
reasons without knowledge of the situation in that country.
</P>
<P>
It cited a case in which a Ghanaian pastor who traveled to
China apparently to conduct crusade with the notion that China is
a Christian country.
</P>
<P>
The release pledged the ministry's readiness to assist
would-be travelers in such circumstances. 
