<HEADLINE> Russian New MIG-29SMT Fighter Put Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The first serial updated
MIG-29SMT fighter was rolled out of the Russian experimental MIG
factory on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The new jet will fly to the center of training and re-training
of Russian Air Force personnel in the city of Lipetsk early next
year where its service testing will start, MIG-29 chief designer
Valeri Novikov was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Defense Ministry took a decision early this year on
serial overhauling of 150-180 MIG-29 fighters into a MIG-29SMT
version and on armying the Russian Air Force with these jets,
Novikov said.
</P>
<P>
According to the chief designer, only MIG-29 fighters, put out
over the past decade, will be overhauled. This will help to raise
steeply combat capabilities of the Russian Air Force up to the
year of 2020.
</P>
<P>
It was said that the overhauling of the MIG-29 will raise its
combat efficiency eight times.
</P>
<P>
Novikov said the jet has now become a multi-purpose aircraft,
performing the functions of a fighter, interceptor, attack plane,
reconnaissance aircraft or an air command post, cooperating with
the A-50, the Russian counterpart of the U.S. AWACS.
</P>
<P>
It can carry any weapons systems, including "air-to-air" and
"air-to-surface" of both Russian and foreign makes, as well as all
types of weapons, used by NATO countries, the chief designer said.
</P>
</TEXT>
