<HEADLINE> Three Britons Killed in Yemen Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook said Tuesday that three British hostages had been killed by
kidnappers in Yemen during an operation to free them Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Cook said he was deeply shocked by the deaths.
He told all remaining Britons in Yemen to leave.
</P>
<P>
The three Britons were among 16 foreign tourists being held by
the militant Islamic Jihad group in Yemen. An Australian was also
killed in the operation.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni government said earlier that all four victims died
when troops attacked the kidnappers.
</P>
<P>
"I am very sorry to confirm that three of the British tourists
have been killed and others injured. Next of kin have been
informed. We understand one Australian has also been killed," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"In light of today's events we've revised our travel advice.
British nationals should not attempt to travel to Yemen unless
their business is essential and any British visitors still there
should leave," he said.
</P>
<P>
It is unclear how many others were injured in the operation,
which resulted in a shoot-out, said Cook.
</P>
<P>
It was also unknown what the Islamic group's motives are in
kidnapping the foreigners, the foreign secretary added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
