<HEADLINE> France Demands Khmer Rouge Leaders Be Put on Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The French government Wednesday
called for the trial of Khieu Samphan and Nuon Chea, the two
recently surrendered Khmer Rouge leaders, saying, "Justice must
be done and all those responsible for these crimes must answer for
 their acts."
</P>
<P>
French government spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said,
"France has always condemned the abomination of this genocide.
The genocide perpetrated by the Khmer Rouge in Cambodia between
1975 and 1979 was one of the greatest tragedies of this century."
</P>
<P>
Paris also said that the defection signalled the end of the
Khmer Rouge's last strongholds in western Cambodia. France hoped
that all the bases of guerrillas in this region will be finally
eliminated.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain have also called for the
holding of judicial procedure against the two Khmer Rouge
leaders. 
</P>
