<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Police Step Up Crackdown on Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Singapore police are
stepping up crackdown on crimes during the current festive season.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested 40 people, mostly drug abusers and illegal
immigrants, after a two-day islandwide crackdown which started at
midnight Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The round-up operation was believed to be part of the police
efforts to curb the crime situation from worsening ahead of the
year-end.
</P>
<P>
Some 150 officers from all seven land divisions of the police,
most in plainclothes, were mobilized to take part in the 30-hour
blitz operation targeting crowded public entertainment areas and
known drug spots.
</P>
<P>
According to reported statistics for the first half of 1998,
crimes of murder, snatch thefts, motor vehicle thefts and rape
increased by 66, 55, 42 and 29 percent respectively. But crime of
rioting declined by 11.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
A senior police officer has affirmed there is no cause for
alarm as the crime situation is still under control in Singapore.
</P>
</TEXT>
