<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, December 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES -- An online bookstore will offer American college
students up to 110,000 textbook titles and other required course
material, Follett Corporation, a U.S. company announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Follett Corporation, which has provided products and services
to the educational marketplace for 125 years, said that the new
service will be launched when the site efollett.com goes live in
early January. (US-Online Bookstore)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Ten rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party
(PKK) were killed in recent military operations launched by the
Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule of Turkey on Wednesday said that the security forces had
killed nine PKK militants in Kulp town of Diyarbakir province and
one in Kozluk town of Batman province. (Turkey-Killing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- Sri Lankan government troops Tuesday killed nine
Tamil rebels in Northern Province of the country, a military
spokesman said here Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops at
Vannivilankulam confronted a group of Tamil rebels and killed
five rebels.
</P>
<P>
In another incident at Oddusudan, troops conducted a small
group operation and killed one rebel. (Sri Lanka-Tamil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- About 300,000 people lost their jobs in Thailand
in the past year to be victims of the financial crisis, the Thai
News Agency Wednesday quoted Labor Minister Sompong Amonvivat as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Most of the jobless, 280,000, were laid off from their
companies, the minister noted. (Thailand-Unemployment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Union statistics office, Eurostat,
reported on Wednesday that inflation in the 11 single currency
euro zone countries fell from one percent to 0.9 percent in
October.
</P>
<P>
In the 15 countries of the European Union inflation in
November was one percent, down from 1.1 percent in October. A
year ago it was 1.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The low inflation rate provides an ideal environment into
which the single currency is due to be launched within 36 hours.
(EU-Inflation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- An Israeli soldier was killed and two others
wounded in a friendly fire accident in south Lebanon overnight.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when two parts of Israeli troops
exchanged fire after they mistook the other side for "terrorists"
near Taibe in the central security zone in south Lebanon.
(Israel-Lebanon-Soldier)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- A British warplane patrolling in the southern
no-fly zone in Iraq came under attack of Iraqi missiles shortly
after Wednesday noon.
</P>
<P>
U.S. sources said the U.S. warplanes came to the British
plane's help after the attack was launched. U.S. fighter jets
fired missiles and laser-guided bombs on an Iraqi missile site.
</P>
<P>
All British and U.S. planes have safely returned to their
bases. (Iraq-Britain-Attack) 
</P>
