and damages. Maj Joe LcMarca of the U.S. Central Command told CNN
that "We are in a process of damage assessment" and said he
believed "our ammunitions are accurate."
</P>
<P>
The northern and southern no-fly zones in Iraq were imposed by
the U.S. and its allies in 1991 and 1992 respectively, with
claimed aims of protecting Kurds and Shiite Muslims from troops of
President Saddam Hussein.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Vice President Taha Yassin Ramadan has declared that his
government does not recognize the no-fly zones, set up "illegally"
by the U.S. and its allies without U.N. authorization, and
demanded that the U.N. discuss this issue.
</P>
<P>
"We are operating normally" in these zones, said Ramadan,
meaning Iraqi planes will defy the fly ban and challenge the
U.S. in the areas.
</P>
<P>
U.S. and British forces gathering in the Gulf carried out four
consecutive nights of air strikes against Iraq December 16-19 to
punish Baghdad for not cooperating fully in U.N. weapons
inspections.
</P>
<P>
With their hope for an early lifting of crippling U.N.
sanctions dashed by the air raids, the Iraqis seemed to have
changed their tactics by barring the return of U.N. weapons
inspectors and challenging the U.S. in the no-fly zones.
</P>
<P>
This threatens to turn U.S.-Iraq confrontation into a daily
recurrence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981230.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Starts Construction of Widest Yangtze River Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China today began the
construction of a new bridge, the widest so far over the Yangtze
River, at a location southwest of Wuhan, capital of central
China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The bridge, named the Junshan Yangtze River Bridge, will be
five kilometers long, including the bridge approach, and 33.5
meters wide.
</P>
<P>
When completed in 2002, the bridge will have six lanes designed
for speeds up to 120 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is being built at a cost of 1.3 billion yuan (about
157 million U.S. dollars) and is an important section of the
Beijing-Zhuhai Expressway, which is also under construction.
</P>
<P>
The expressway is expected to be completed in 2002, and will
become a major artery connecting north and south China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
