<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Sends New Year Messages to Foreign Counterparts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
criticized the U.S. air strikes against Iraq, describing them as
"unacceptable", in a New Year message to U.S. President Bill
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The seasonal greeting was one of a series sent to foreign
leaders, including his counterparts of the Commonwealth of
Independent States, presidential spokesman Dmitri Yakushkin said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
