Chirac, German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder, British Prime
Minister Tony Blair and Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi.
</P>
<P>
Yakushkin said Yeltsin had told Chirac that Russia and France
enjoyed a "privileged partnership" and the two countries shared
the same opinion on most international issues, including the
recent crisis in Iraq. 
