<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldier Killed by Friendly Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, December 30 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier was killed
and two others wounded in a friendly fire accident in south
Lebanon overnight.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when two parts of Israeli troops
exchanged fire after they mistook the other side for "terrorists"
near Taibe in the central security zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
"As a result of a split in the troops, the rear part of the
troops saw the front part and mistook them for terrorists,"
according to the Orient radio.
</P>
<P>
The death raised to 24 the number of the Israeli soldiers
killed in south Lebanon since the start of this year. Thirty
seven guerrillas, mostly from the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or
Party of God, have also been killed over the same period.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a self-declared security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with a claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting against Israeli occupation. 
