<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
decided to grant a new general amnesty to army deserters effective
from January 1 to 5 next year, said a military spokesman Wednesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said the amnesty was granted following
requests by parents of the deserters and indications of the
deserters who have already reported back for duty.
</P>
