<HEADLINE> Yearender: HK Signs Record Number of Agreements With Foreign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong has over the years signed air services agreements
with 34 countries, of which 13 were sealed after Hong Kong
returned to China. The signing of the agreements has provided
convenience for the expansion of ties between Hong Kong and these
countries in the fields of economy, trade and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has also concluded accords for the promotion and
protection of investments with 15 countries. Under the agreements,
 the two sides provide for equal treatment of investors and for
the settlement of investment disputes in accordance with
international norms. As a result, the interests of investors are
fully guaranteed and Hong Kong's position as a financial and
trade center has been strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Hong Kong has signed agreements on the surrender of
fugitive offenders with 11 countries, accords on the transfer of
sentenced persons with two countries, and agreements on mutual
legal assistance in criminal matters with seven countries.
</P>
<P>
These have laid a legal basis for joint crackdown on criminal
offense, and provided a guarantee for maintaining social
stability.
</P>
<P>
All this shows that Hong Kong's relationship with foreign
countries has been greatly expanded since its return to China.
</P>
<P>
"The signing by Hong Kong of a host of bilateral agreements
with foreign countries after its return to China demonstrates the
Central People's Government's respect for 'Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong' and full trust in the SAR government under
the principle of 'one country, two systems'," Ma said.
</P>
<P>
This is of great significance for ensuring Hong Kong's position
as an international financial, trading and shipping center and
maintaining its long-term prosperity and stability, he added.
</P>
