<HEADLINE> Some 300,000 Thais Lost Jobs in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 30 (Xinhua) -- About 300,000 people lost
their jobs in Thailand in the past year to be victims of the
financial crisis, the Thai News Agency Wednesday quoted Labor
Minister Sompong Amonvivat as saying.
</P>
<P>
Most of the jobless, 280,000, were laid off from their
companies, the minister noted.
</P>
<P>
To cope with the situation, the ministry has launched several
measures to help the unfortunate, including the creation of new
jobs in rural areas, industrial and service sectors, the
repatriation of a total of 300,000 alien workers, a project to
promote individual careers and a scheme to send Thai workers
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Sompong said redundancies should stop in the second quarter of
next year as the Thai economy was expected to pick up then.
</P>
<P>
Redundancies would slow down in the first quarter and stop in
the second, then more employment should happen in the third
quarter, the minister said. 
</P>
