<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Model Village Prospers Under Market Economy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today, Guo, the then nicknamed "iron-girl", embraces the market
economy with the firmness and vigor she exerted in pursuing
revolutionary truth in the past. She has traveled far and wide,
trying to bring outside investment to Dazhai or is busy promoting
locally made products. This, say other villagers, demonstrates her
competence as a business woman under the new market economy system.
</P>
<P>
Under her leadership, Dazhai Village has given up the extensive
"self-sufficient" economy for which it was famous and prosperous
and set up manufacturing businesses. The 52-year-old Guo Fenglian
is now chairman of the board and general manager of the Dazhai
Economic Development Company.
</P>
<P>
But many Dazhai villagers are not keen to discuss their past
and many seem to be disillusioned by it.
</P>
<P>
Part of the reason may be that when China introduced the reform
and opening-up policy in 1978, the people of Dazhai were not too
impressed and were slow to adapt to the new system. The household
responsibility system was introduced to Dazhai late in 1983, thus
putting an end to the communal activities they had been used to.
</P>
<P>
In the remaining years of the 1980s and the beginning of the
1990s, Dazhai was out of the public eye. It wasn't until 1991,
when Guo Fenglian returned to Dazhai after working away for many
years in a local fruit-tree research institute, that the village
began to catch up with both China and the world's development.
</P>
<P>
Guo has proved her worth as a good business woman . In 1992, when
she attended the 14th National Congress of the Chinese Communist
Party in Beijing as a delegate, she took along dozens of sweaters
made by the Dazhai Sweater Mill and gave them as gifts to many
delegates. This has helped market and promote the sweaters across
China.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Dazhai Village took over the Xiyang County Distillery
and formed the Dazhai Distillery Co. Ltd., signing a contract with
the Laojiao Distillery of Ningcheng, Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region to employ experts to show them how to run it. The new
company soon began making the "Dazhai Chun" brand of clear liquor
and has so far sold more than 1,600 tons.
</P>
<P>
Now, most of the residents say that they are more content with
their new life styles, as they are not only prosperous but also can
speak their minds without fear of being punished, as they were in
the past.
</P>
<P>
Even though young people riding around on motorcycles or
watching television are not so familiar with the ways of their
elders, they do admire the spirit of the older generation which
helped build the modern day Dazhai which they now enjoy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981230.0116 </DOCNO>
