<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Closes Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed firmer
on the Singapore Stock Market Wednesday buoyed by the overnight
rally on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) finished 16.25 points
up at 1394.70 points after a quiet session.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover increased to 133.98 million units worth
180.11 million Singapore dollars (about 108.62 million U.S.
dollars). Gainers outnumbered losers by 212 to 47 with 161
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was a 7.74 million parcel of KepTLDBS w00
which transacted at 00.615 Singapore dollars per share. Brilliant
was the second most heavily traded stock with a volume of 6.69
million units done. LungKee was next with 5.12 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 topped the rises chart of the day surging up 70
cents to finish at 23.00 Singapore dollars. SemMarLog climbed up
37 cents to close at 2.70 Singapore dollars. OUT F was up 29 cents
to end at 1.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SIA F was the biggest loser of the day
retreating 30 cents to close at 12.30 Singapore dollars. Robinson
was next shedding 24 cents to 3.56 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem
and Jurship sank 20 cents and ended at 8.50 and 7.15 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market rose from the start of the dealings
following Wall Street's overnight rally.
</P>
<P>
Prices gained on selective year-end window dressing and some
buying in smaller-capitalized issues, they added.
</P>
<P>
They also noted that investors were warming to expectations
that the local bourse will start the new year on a bullish note,
picking up from the recent rally interrupted by holidays and book
closure ahead of the launch of the Euro. 
</P>
