<HEADLINE> King Hussein Leaves Hospital after Cancer Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, December 30 (Xinhua) - Jordanian King Hussein Ibn
Talal Tuesday left a U.S. hospital where he received six rounds of
chemotherapy for lymphatic cancer.
</P>
<P>
In a letter addressed to the Jordanian people, King Hussein
said that he was allowed to leave the hospital as results of the
tests conducted in the past few days were better than the doctors
had expected.
</P>
<P>
The king said he had also undergone a bone marrow transplant
after ablation of lymphoma cells in the bone marrow in the Mayo
Clinic at Rochester, Minnesota, the U.S., where he had been
hospitalized since July 14.
</P>
<P>
Hussein said he will stay in Washington and London for a
couple of days for full recovery before returning to Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian Crown Prince and the Regent Hassan Ibn Talal said
Tuesday evening that his brother ``has fully recovered from his
illness", and will be returning to Jordan soon.
</P>
<P>
Hussein delegated all powers to the Regent during his stay in
the U.S. hospital, except the rights of signing major
international accords and making amendments to the constitution of
the kingdom. 
</P>
