<HEADLINE> Sihanouk Not to Sign Amnesty for Khmer Rouge Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian King Norodom
Sihanouk said Tuesday that he will not sign any amnesty for any
Khmer Rouge leaders from now on, including newly-defected Khmer
Rouge leaders Khieu Samphan and Nuon Chea.
</P>
<P>
The king, who is in Beijing for a routine health checkup, made
the remarks in his royal palace bulletin which was distributed
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"From now on, I leave all the responsibility to (Prime
Minister) Hun Sen of handling this unfortunate and dramatic thing
of pardon to the Khmer Rouge. I will not sign any decrees
concerning the Khmer Rouge," said the monarch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
