<HEADLINE> Another Telecom Complex Bombed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 30 (Xinhua) -- A high powered bomb Tuesday
night blasted the telecom complex in Ampara town of Eastern Sri
Lanka, the evening newspaper The Observer reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Immediate investigations revealed that the damage to the
complex is high and may take long to repair. Fortunately, the
communication facilities remain intact, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said the explosion took place in the generator room
around 11.30 p.m.. Investigators suspect it to be a time bomb laid
by Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
Combined police and army units continue to search the place to
see whether any more bombs are planted.
</P>
<P>
There had been another telecom blast in Galle of Southern Sri
Lanka early Tuesday. A telecommunications facility at the Galle
junction was extensively damaged in a bomb attack by suspected
Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
At least 15 telecommunications buildings and electrical
transformers in separate provinces have been exploded in May and
June this year by Tamil rebels who are fighting for a separate
state in the north and east of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
