<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Entry-Exit Permit More Convenient for HK, Macao Compatriots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- A new type of entry-exit
permit will be issued to Hong Kong and Macao compatriots starting
from January 15, 1999, an official from the Exit and Entry
Administration under the Ministry of Public Security announced
today.
</P>
<P>
It will be much more convenient and easy to use and has
in-built anti-forgery functions.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the "Return-Home Certificate for Hong
Kong and Macao Compatriots", which was introduced in 1978, has not
kept pace with technology since China began its opening-up policy
20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The new entry-exit inspection departments will have electronic
scanners, instead of relying on manual checks, to identify the new
permits and record all the information needed.
</P>
<P>
The credit card size certificate has a ten-year validity period.
</P>
<P>
According to China's laws, all Hong Kong and Macao residents,
whether in possession of foreign passports and tourist
certificates or not, are entitled to apply for the new entry-exit
permit, as long as they do not apply to the Chinese authorities
for foreign registration.
</P>
<P>
All Hong Kong and Macao compatriots under the age of 18 are
entitled to apply for a permit with a validity period of three
years, and those 18 and above for a ten year permit.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the Ministry of Public Security will
stop issuing the old Return-Home Certificates from January 1st,
1999, but that all existing permits issued before this date can be
used up to the expiry period.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Security has authorized the Hong Kong
and Macao branches of the China Travel Service to provide
information about the new permits for applicants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
