<DOCNO> XIE19981230.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oil Refinery to Be Built in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANNOI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese government gave
license to a Vietnamese-Russian joint-venture to build and run an
oil refinery, the English daily Vietnam News reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The joint-venture, established on November 19 this year, is
called Vietross Refinery. The 25-year joint-venture has a
projected investment capital of 1.3 billion U.S. dollars, funded
equally by its two partners -- Vietnam's sole oil and gas
operator, Petro Vietnam, and Russia's External Economic
Federation, Zarubeznheft.
</P>
<P>
The joint-venture should be able to refine 6.5 million tons of
crude oil per year. A major source of material for the Dung Quat
oil refinery will be Vietnam's crude oil.
</P>
<P>
This is the second oil joint-venture between Vietnam and
Russia. The first oil production joint-venture between Vietnam and
Russia was Vietsovpetro, which was established in 1986. It has
been Vietnam's major crude oil producer ever since -- its crude
oil volume accounts for about 80 percent of Vietnam's total
output.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has produced 12.6 million tons of crude oil this year
and all most of all the crude oil has been exported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
