<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Remains at 5.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Macao
remained at 5.4 percent in the September-November period this
year, latest official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released Wednesday by the Macao Census and
 Statistics Department, the jobless rate was the same as that in
the August-October period this year, but up 2.5 percent from that
between September and November last year.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from workers' unions in Macao have proposed
that the government employ more local labor instead of outside
labor in public projects and service trades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
