<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CNPC Producing High Profits, Taxes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The China National Petroleum
Corp (CNPC) is expected to realize 29.75 billion yuan in profits
and taxes this year despite declining oil prices worldwide and the
Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to a CNPC source, the corporation is expected to have
turned out more than 100 million tons of crude oil and nearly 14.9
billion cu m of natural gas by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
A senior CNPC official noted that China's petroleum industry
has been seriously affected by the Asian financial crisis
and the declining oil markets worldwide.
</P>
<P>
To make it worse, the domestic demand for crude oil and
refined oil products was slackening and smuggling rampant.
</P>
<P>
Facing such difficulties, China has reduced imports of crude
oil and related products, increased the domestic supply for
foreign-funded enterprises and made efforts to crack down on oil
smuggling, effectively reducing the effects of falling oil prices.
</P>
<P>
The official said that China has also strengthened
macro-control over crude and related oil products markets and
promoted the rational distribution of crude and related oil
products resources.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has accelerated its reform of the oil
circulation and pricing systems and reshaped the China National
Petroleum (CNPC) Corp. and the China National Petrochemical Corp
(Sinopec).
</P>
<P>
Under the new oil system, China has combined upstream and
downstream production, in addition to integrating internal and
external trade.
</P>
<P>
The CNPC source said that it discovered three oil and gas
fields this year, each with oil reserves exceeding 100 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, CNPC verified 485 million tons of oil and 223.2
billion cu m of natural gas this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
