<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New PBOC Branches to Begin Operation on January 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China
(PBOC), China's central bank, announced today that its newly
established branches will be open for business from January 1,
1999.
</P>
<P>
Following a decision by the State Council, the PBOC carried out
a significant reform of its administrative system by establishing
nine regional branches to replace its original branches in
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The new branches are located in Tianjin, Shenyang, Shanghai,
Nanjing, Jinan, Wuhan, Guangzhou, Chengdu and Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
In addition, two business administration offices of the PBOC
will be set up in Beijing and Chongqing to replace the original
PBOC branches in the two cities.
</P>
<P>
The work of the new branches will be to implement the state's
related laws, regulations, principles and policies, while
comprehensively supervising and administering the business
activities of the financial institutions under its jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
They will also be responsible for managing the central bank's
monetary and credit policy business including capital, deposited
reserves, interest rates and cash management, as well as analyzing
each region's financial situation and financial risks.
</P>
<P>
The announcement also gave details about the establishment of
financial supervisory offices and central sub-branches of the PBOC
in provincial capital cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
