<HEADLINE> 10 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Ten rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in recent military
operations launched by the Turkish security forces in
southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional Rule
of Turkey on Wednesday said that the security forces had killed
nine PKK militants in Kulp town of Diyarbakir province and one in
Kozluk town of Batman province.
</P>
<P>
Two PKK guerrillas surrendered to the security forces in the
region, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old separatist war for
autonomy in southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over 37,000
lives in conflicts since August 1984. 
