<HEADLINE> 32 Injured in Road Accident in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- A passenger bus fell Wednesday
morning into a ravine along a zigzag road in a Northern Philippine
province, injuring 32 people, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said the driver of the north-bound bus lost control of
the vehicle which over-shot a sharp curve and plunged into a
16-feet deep ravine in the village of Lungib, Calauag, Quezon
Province.
</P>
<P>
Police said the bus, carrying some 50 passengers, was on its
way from Manila to the Southeastern Daet town in the Bicol Region,
when its wheels slipped through a muddy road amid heavy rains
along the national highway in Calauag.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers pulled up the passengers from the windows of the bus,
and the injured passengers were rushed to a nearby hospital for
treatment, police said. 
</P>
