<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Garment Manufacturer Issues B-Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Matsuoka Co. Ltd., a
Sino-Japanese garment manufacturer registered in the city's New
Pudong Area, has just issued 110 million B-shares for overseas
investors.
</P>
<P>
The shares carried an initial public offering (IPO) price of
0.28 US dollar each.
</P>
<P>
Shenyin Wanguo Securities Corp. served as lead underwriter for
the issue. Shenyin Wanguo President Wang Yuchun said overseas
investors have welcomed the issue, the first B-share issue in six
months. Wang's company has now issued a total of 38 B-shares.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture's B shares were mostly bought by overseas
investors and mutual fund management companies. The
weighted market earning ratio is 3.81 times the issue price.
</P>
<P>
The issue will end today and the shares will be traded on
the stock exchange before January 21 next year.
</P>
<P>
B-shares, and A-shares -- designed for domestic investors --
are the two major kinds of shares that are traded on stock bourses
in China. As a step to standardize operations in the securities
market, China's Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress adopted a Securities Law which was promulgated in Beijing
on December 29.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Matsuoka Co. Ltd., founded in 1990 between Pinghu
Xincang No. 1 Mill of Zhejiang Province and Matsuoka Company of
Japan, is mainly engaged in making uniforms for export, with an
annual production capacity of 15 million items and an annual
output value exceeding 800 million yuan. The joint venture also
holds 40 percent of the stake in the Matsuoka Printing Co. Ltd..
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will use the money raised through the share
issue to build a new manufacturing factory, starting up a
materials distribution center, purchasing the remaining 60 percent
of the stake in Matsuoka Printing Co. Ltd., as well as building a
clothing marketing and product exhibition center in Pudong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
