<HEADLINE> China To Maintain Order of Festive Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Government watchdogs have
stepped-up measures to prevent shoddy and inferior products from
entering the market during the New Year's and Spring Festival
periods.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration of Industry and Commerce recently
issued a circular urging all localities to maintain the
market order during the two festivals which are traditionally the
busiest shopping periods of the year.
</P>
<P>
Measures have been introduced to prevent price gouging and
cheating on the grain and sideline products markets which are
mainly operated by peddlers.
</P>
<P>
Production and sales of popular festival items such as spirits,
soft drinks and meat will be closely monitored.
</P>
<P>
The administration also called for intensive examinations of
open markets, restaurants and hotels to prevent sales of
endangered plants and animals under the state protection.
</P>
<P>
Plans also call for an intense campaign to prevent the spread
of pornographic material via books, computers, Internet bars and
videos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
