<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Approves Chittagong Master Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
approved a 20-year master plan for the country's second largest
city of Chittagong, said press reports reaching here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Situated in the southeastern part of the country, Chittagong is
also Bangladesh's biggest seaport city with a population of about
six million.
</P>
<P>
Works of formulation of the master plan started in April 1992
with the financial and technical assistance of the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) and concluded in June 1995.
</P>
<P>
The plan, which was finally approved by the Works Ministry this
week, has 76 guidelines including a 10-year urban development
project and two detail area plans aiming at the development of the
city to cope with the needs of the next century.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, employment opportunity for 0.45 million
people should be created in next 20 years to face the pressure of
population, which is increasing by 42,000 annually in the city.
</P>
<P>
In order to implement the plan, 90 hectares of land will be
needed each year for the housing of the increased population.
</P>
<P>
The reports, however, did not mention the total investment for
implementing the plan and where the fund will come from. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
