<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Spokesman Addresses Japanese Decisions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu
Bangzao said today that China sincerely hopes Japan will strictly
abide by a defense policy limited to its own territory and coastal
waters, and adhere to a peaceful development path.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark today when commenting on the Japanese
government's recent decision to launch four military
reconnaissance satellites in the year 2002, and join the United
States in researching the Theater Missile Defense (TMD) program
from 1999.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China is deeply concerned about the
political and military connotation of the aforementioned moves, as
well as their possible impact on regional and global security.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that peace and development have been the theme of the
times since the end of the Cold War. He stressed that the
development and spread of a strategic arms system under such
circumstances could possibly spark arms races and harm both the
global strategic balance and stability.  
</P>
</TEXT>
