<HEADLINE> China's Real Estate Market Thriving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate sector
maintained a strong growth momentum in the first eleven months of
1998, according to Ye Zhen, spokesman for the National Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
He said at a press conference today that China invested 249
billion yuan in real estate during that period, up 18.3 percent
over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Housing with a total floor space of 72.76 million square meters
was completed, up 20 percent, with the sales of floor space up
48.1 percent and turnover up 50.4 percent, respectively. Sales of
housing to individuals jumped 64.7 percent. 
</P>
