<HEADLINE> Textile Exports Down Four Percent In Ten Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's textile industry
recorded a total foreign trade volume of 45.85 billion US dollars
in the first 10 months of the year, according to the Chinese
language International Business News.
</P>
<P>
The paper run by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation says exports stood at 33.93 billion US dollars, down
3.9 percent on the previous year's period, with imports dropping
1.5 percent to 11.92 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Textile exports normally account for close to one fourth of
China's total foreign trade volume.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper attributes slumping textile exports to the
financial crisis in Asia and efforts to trim the overgrown
domestic textile industry.  
</P>
