<HEADLINE> Estrada Optimistic About Philippines' Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines "has good
prospects in completely getting out of the Asian crisis" through
political will and determination of its people in 1999, said
President Joseph Estrada.
</P>
<P>
In his new year message released here Wednesday, Estrada said
that the past year has been one of the most trying times for the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
"The currency crisis that hit the Asian region has slowed down
the region's economic progress. While the adverse effects may be
worse in other countries, yet we cannot be more confident than
them with the decline in available jobs and the increase in the
prices of basic commodities," he said.
</P>
<P>
Despite the difficulties, Estrada said, Filipinos have remained
undaunted.
</P>
<P>
"We shall welcome the new year with high hopes and
determination. As we continue to move forward in 1999, expect us
to undertake more initiatives to attract greater investments from
our overseas friends," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our strong points lie in our strategic location in Asia, our
large domestic market dominated by a young population base and our
abundant supply of high-trainable, highly-skilled and
English-speaking human resources," he said.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, Estrada said, the Philippines can boast of an
improved peace and order situation in the new year. 
</P>
