<HEADLINE> Slovakia's GDP Grows by 5.8 Percent in First Nine Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia's economy continued a
high upturn momentum during the first nine months of this year,
with the gross domestic product (GDP)growing by 535.4 billion
korun (15.7 billion U.S. dollars), an increase of 5.8 percent ov
er the same period last year, the local media reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Local media reports quoted the Slovak State Statistics Bureau
as saying that the GDP is expected to growth 5.9 percent in the
whole of this year, slightly down from last year's level of 6.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
The local media said Slovakia is one of the economies having
the highest growth in the central-eastern European region in 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, the Slovak economy is still plagued by such problems
as rising trade deficits, a high unemployment rate and huge
foreign debts, media reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
