<HEADLINE> China's Exports Match Last Year's Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's exports in 1998 are
expected to reach 182 billion U.S. dollars, roughly matching last
year's level, according to Ye Zhen, spokesman for the National
Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Ye told a press conference today that the country's imports for
1998 are estimated at 137 billion U.S. dollars, down 3.8
percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
The trade surplus in 1998 will be about 45 billion
U.S. dollars, an increase of 4.7 billion U.S. dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the amount of foreign investment actually used in
the year is projected at 54 billion U.S. dollars. 
