<HEADLINE> 5 Killed in Floods in Indonesia's Central Java </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed in
floods in Indonesia's Central Java province Sunday, reports from
the province said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The latest victim was a woman found in the Cirongkang river in
Banyumas district Monday afternoon. The woman died after a strong
current swept her away when she and her husband were crossing a
bridge, the Jakarta Post reported.
</P>
<P>
An entire family of four was killed in Duren village of Bawang
district. Their home was hit by a landslide early Sunday and the
bodies could only be recovered in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Banyumas regent Aris Setiono told reporters that the floods
were caused by the overflowing of the Klawing river passing
Purbalingga, Banyumas and Kebumen. Thousands of residents took
refuge and were provided with meals by the local administrations,
while thousands of hectares of crops were flooded.
</P>
<P>
In Jakarta, the ministry of public works said it was allocating
up to 15 billion rupiah (1.25 million U.S. dollars) in emergency
funds in the wake of the floods.
</P>
<P>
The funds are part of a 400 billion rupiah budget for floods,
the director general of water works, Budiman Arif was quoted by
the Jakarta Post as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
