<HEADLINE> China's Fixed Asset Investment Up 15 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's investment in fixed
assets in 1998 is expected to reach 2.868 trillion yuan, up 15
percent from last year, Ye Zhen, spokesman for the National Bureau
of Statistics, announced today.
</P>
<P>
Ye said at a press conference that state-owned
institutions invested a total of 2.15 trillion yuan in fixed
assets, up 22 percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
He said that investment by state-owned institutions has been on
the increase, with growth rates hitting at 10.3 percent, 15.2
percent, 28.2 percent and 24 percent in the four quarters,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
"Accelerated investment has been a major factor spurring
economic expansion," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the increased investment has been designed for
infrastructure construction and the development of basic
industries, with priority given to central and western China.
