<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Incremental Value up 8.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial incremental
value is expected to increase by 8.8 percent on a yearly basis to
2.012 trillion yuan in 1998, according to the National Bureau of
Statistics today.
</P>
<P>
The value produced by state-owned industrial enterprises and
state-controlled firms was up 4.8 percent, while that of collective
industrial enterprises rose 8.8 percent and that of industrial
firms of other types jumped 13.5 percent, Bureau spokesman Ye Zhen
told a press conference this morning.
</P>
<P>
As China's measures to boost domestic demand began to show
effects, industrial growth accelerated in the second half of
1998, Ye said, adding that the growth rate reached 8.6 percent in
the third quarter and 11 percent in the fourth quarter, as against
7.8 percent for the first half of 1998. 
</P>
