<HEADLINE> Botha Foresees Fight with Tyson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Francois Botha of South
Africa says he will turn into another Evander Holyfield when he
fights Mike Tyson on January 16.
</P>
<P>
"I'm going to fight him the way Holyfield fought him," Botha
said. "If you look at Tyson's fights when he gets hurt, it is
when you are the first to punch. You can't stand in front of him
and do nothing and close up and let him pick his shots like a lot
of guys like (Bruce) Seldon and (Frank) Bruno did."
</P>
<P>
Botha will fight Tyson on January 16 at the MGM Grand Hotel
and Casino.
</P>
<P>
"You've got to push him around, wrestle him and hold him like
Holyfield did. That is the way to get him in the later rounds,"
said Botha, who has a 39-1 record with 24 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the public still see him as the baddest man out
there and people who don't know me will think they will never see
Francois Botha alive again. Just imagine after I beat Mike Tyson
what they will say then. My victory will be that much sweeter
because no one gave me a chance. After this fight I will get the
respect that I deserve," Botha said. 
