<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nine District Heads, One Mayor Fired by Indonesian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Home Affairs
Minister Syarwan Hamid Tuesday said nine district heads and a
mayor were recently discharged from their positions for
involvement in corrupt, collusive and nepotistic practices.
</P>
<P>
The measure was a follow-up to a decree of the People's
Consultative Assembly (MPR) number 11/1998, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Article 4 of the decree states that efforts to eradicate
corruption, collusion and nepotism must be made indiscriminately
upon any state officials, former state officials, their families
and cronies as well as private businessmen, business tycoons and
former president Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
The minister said five of the district heads and the mayor of
Tegal in Central Java were servicemen, while the rest were civil
servants.
</P>
<P>
He also said public prosecutor's offices were handling corrupt,
collusive and nepotistic practices which involved another nine
district heads and mayor of Ujungpandang in South Sulawesi.
</P>
<P>
Mayor of Jambi in Sumatera island was interrogated by the Jambi
police and public prosecutor's office, alleging bought votes in
the election of a village head, Hamid was quoted by Antara News
Agency Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Southeast Maluku district head was strongly believed
to have embezzled 4 billion rupiah (one U.S. dollars equals 8,000
rupiah), and involved in collusive practices and fake projects
which had caused a loss of 25 billion rupiah and 2.2 billion
rupiah respectively to the state.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the Aceh Barat, Asahan and Batang Hari
district heads in Sumatera island had also been found involved in
irregularities.
</P>
<P>
According to Coordinating Minister for Development
Supervision/State Reform Hartarto, the Indonesian state suffered
financial losses totaling 2,850 billion rupiah by corrupt,
collusive and nepotistic practices involving Soeharto,
high-ranking officials of his government and his cronies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
