<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti World's Top International Football Scorer for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Jassem al-Houwaidi of Kuwait is
football's top international goal scorer for 1998, having hit the
back of the net 20 times for his country in the course of the
year, the International Federation for Football History and Sta
tistics (IFFHS) announced Tuesday in Wiesbaden.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old al-Houwaidi, a teacher who only plays in his
spare time as an amateur for the Al-Salmiya club in the Kuwaiti
first division, succeeds Ronaldo, who scored 22 goals for Brazil
and in international club competitions in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Second place in 1998 went to Gabriel Batistuta of Argentina
and Fiorentina (Italy), with 14 goals, while Luis Hernandez of
Mexico and Necaxa FC (Mexico City), with 13. 
</P>
