<HEADLINE> Beijing Youth Respect Scientists Most </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- More than half of the young
people in Beijing think scientists have made greater contributions
to society than entrepreneurs, according to a recent survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by the Beijing Shaohai Market Research
Company, revealed that scientists are the professionals most
respected by Beijing youth, followed by soldiers and middle and
primary school teachers. Journalists, workers and movie stars have
the lowest esteem among this group.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted among Beijing residents aged between 14
and 35, found that 53.2 percent of the respondents believe
scientists make greater contributions to society than
entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
This shows that they have a good understanding of Deng
Xiaoping's statement that "science and technology is the first
productive force," said the market researchers.
</P>
<P>
The survey was designed to study scientific awareness among
Beijing's younger population. Twenty-nine percent of the
respondents are college graduates, 43 percent have high school
educations, and 28 percent are below the junior high school level.
</P>
<P>
It shows that 89 percent of the respondents think their
scientific knowledge is insufficient, while 40 percent desire more
computer-related knowledge, and 59 percent said they don't have
enough time to acquire all the knowledge they would like.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
