<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks Soar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street share prices
soared Tuesday with the blue-chip indicator approaching its
November 23 peak.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 94.23 or 1 percent to
9,320.98, supported by a strong consumer confidence report.
</P>
<P>
The index extended a seven session winning streak with a total
gain of 530 points since December 17. It is now 17.9 percent up
for the year and only 53 points below the record high of 9,374.27.
</P>
<P>
The Conference Board said Tuesday that despite a slight drop in
consumer confidence in December, Americans are still positive
about the current economic situation.
</P>
<P>
Retail shares gained as positive forecasts for growth in 1999
boosted the sector. But shares of the larger Internet companies,
which have posted enormous gains recently, fell amid
profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index, a broader measure of market
activity, was trading in record territory, up 16.32 to 1,241.81,
leaving it 28 percent above the year's starting point.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 1.47 to a new
record high of 2,181.77, a 38.9 percent growth for the year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 582 million shares, modestly higher than Monday's,
changed hands on the New York Stock Exchange where advancers led
decliners 7-5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
