<HEADLINE> King Hussein Released From Hospital After Cancer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan was
allowed to leave a Minnesota clinic Tuesday as "good health" has
returned after several months of treatment for cancer, a clinic
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"He was in good health," said Jane Jacobs, the spokesman for
the Mayo Clinic in Rochester, Minnesota. "He was in good spirits,
obviously relieved to be out of the hospital."
</P>
<P>
The 63-year-old king was traveling to Washington, D.C., where
he may meet with President Bill Clinton as well as Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright, a Jordanian Embassy spokesman said in
Washington. But no times have been fixed.
</P>
<P>
The king checked into the Mayo Clinic in mid-July, and was
diagnosed with lymphoma and had six cycles of chemotherapy.
</P>
<P>
The king intermittently left the hospital between chemotherapy
treatments.
</P>
<P>
He left the clinic for several days in October to help engineer
the Wye Plantation agreement between Israel and the Palestinians
over the Israeli pullout of 13 percent of the West Bank. 
