<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Get Tiny Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- European stock markets won tiny
gains Tuesday as the countdown to the euro gathering pace and
trading across all the markets was extremely limited.
</P>
<P>
The London market ended on a high on the first day of trading
after Christmas. The FTSE 100 ran up more than 1 percent, 74
points, to close at 5,941.5.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to hold onto the gains until 1999 with
just a half-day of trading Wednesday before dealers stay away for
the New Year break.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Xetra DAX made repeated attempts to move ahead, but
kept falling back until the Dow's initial gains helped it up. The
index rose just 16 points to close at 5,056.20.
</P>
<P>
In Paris some end-of-year window dressing in meager volume
squeezed Paris stocks higher in early afternoon, but the CAC 40
index could not manage more than a 20 point gain and rise of 18
points to finish at 3,891.10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
